<p>Looking back at the lists, among the 'uninteresting' nouns we see 2 that consistently occur:<em>room</em> and <em>night</em>. Incidentally many of the auther's encounters with other persons occur at this place (his room) at this time.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Word2Vec">Word2Vec<a class="anchor-link" href="#Word2Vec">¶</a></h2><p>Finally I take a look at the relationship top words have to each other. To do this, I'll take Google's pre-trained <a href="https://code.google.com/archive/p/word2vec/">word2vec model</a> and extract the word vectors for the top occuring non-neutral terms. Each of these vectors is made up by 300 features, so in order to visualize them I use the <code>tsne</code> library to reduce the dimensions to 2. After this we can plot the words on a 2D space.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [12]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython2"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">## Load Google's model.</span>
<span class="n">gmodel</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">gensim</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">models</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Word2Vec</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">load_word2vec_format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'/model/GoogleNews-vectors-negative300.bin'</span><span class="p">,</span> \
                                                     <span class="n">binary</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">True</span><span class="p">)</span>  
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [79]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython2"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">## Get more words to plot.</span>
<span class="n">commons_ext</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">DataFrame</span><span class="p">({</span><span class="s1">'word'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">word</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">word</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">text_stem</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">most_common</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">700</span><span class="p">)],</span>
                        <span class="s1">'count'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">word</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">word</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">text_stem</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">most_common</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">700</span><span class="p">)],</span>
                        <span class="s1">'score'</span> <span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">afinn</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">score</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">word</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">])</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">word</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">text_stem</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">most_common</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">700</span><span class="p">)]})</span>

<span class="c1">## Get only non-neutral words.</span>
<span class="n">nn_commons_ext</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">commons_ext</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">~</span><span class="n">commons_ext</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'score'</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">isin</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">])]</span>

<span class="c1">## Get word2vec dimensions for top words.</span>
<span class="n">word_x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="n">word_y</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="n">word_c</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="n">word_s</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">r</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">nn_commons_ext</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">iterrows</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">r</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'word'</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">gmodel</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">vocab</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">word_x</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">gmodel</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">r</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'word'</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">encode</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'utf-8'</span><span class="p">)])</span>
        <span class="n">word_y</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">r</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'word'</span><span class="p">])</span>
        <span class="n">word_c</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">r</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'score'</span><span class="p">]))</span>
        <span class="n">word_s</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">r</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'count'</span><span class="p">]))</span>
        
<span class="n">word_x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">word_x</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">astype</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'float64'</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1">## Use t-SNE to reduce dimensions.</span>
<span class="n">word_viz</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">bh_sne</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">word_x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">perplexity</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">8</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [81]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython2"><pre><span></span><span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">rcParams</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'figure.figsize'</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mf">18.0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">18.0</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">cmap</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">ListedColormap</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">palette</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">scatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">word_viz</span><span class="p">[:,</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">word_viz</span><span class="p">[:,</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">c</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">word_c</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">s</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">word_s</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">cmap</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">cmap</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">label</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">zip</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">word_y</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">word_viz</span><span class="p">[:,</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">word_viz</span><span class="p">[:,</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]):</span>
    <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">annotate</span><span class="p">(</span>
        <span class="n">label</span><span class="p">,</span> 
        <span class="n">xy</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">xytext</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">12</span><span class="p">,</span>
        <span class="n">textcoords</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'offset points'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ha</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'right'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">va</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'bottom'</span>
        <span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>We observe a <strong>sex</strong> related cluster at the bottom left side of the plot, and a second <strong>dead</strong> related one on the top. There's also another group near the sex cluster that we can associate with <strong>love</strong>, made up of words such as  kiss, smile, laught and friend. We don't see too much of <strong>alcohol</strong>, which is probably due to these words being filtered out due to their netural sentiment.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Training-a-Word2Vec">Training a Word2Vec<a class="anchor-link" href="#Training-a-Word2Vec">¶</a></h2><p>Now I'll will train our own Word2Vec model, using the corpus of poems as input. First I build a class that yields the sentences, for efficiency, however this is not really required with the scale we are working on.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [184]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython2"><pre><span></span><span class="n">content</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'tokens'</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="c1">## Class to yield lines.</span>
<span class="k">class</span> <span class="nc">LineSet</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">object</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">__init__</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">input_lines</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">input_lines</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">input_lines</span>
 
    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">__iter__</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="bp">self</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">line</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="bp">self</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">input_lines</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="k">yield</span> <span class="n">line</span>
            
<span class="n">line_set</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">LineSet</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">content</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'tokens'</span><span class="p">])</span>

<span class="c1">## Generate model with prunning.</span>
<span class="n">model</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">gensim</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">models</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Word2Vec</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">line_set</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">size</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">200</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">min_count</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">8</span><span class="p">)</span> 
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">

<span class="n">cmap</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">ListedColormap</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">palette</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">scatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">word_viz</span><span class="p">[:,</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">word_viz</span><span class="p">[:,</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">c</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">word_c</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">s</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">word_s</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">cmap</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">cmap</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">label</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">zip</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">word_y</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">word_viz</span><span class="p">[:,</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">word_viz</span><span class="p">[:,</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]):</span>
    <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">annotate</span><span class="p">(</span>
        <span class="n">label</span><span class="p">,</span> 
        <span class="n">xy</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">xytext</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">fontsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">12</span><span class="p">,</span>
        <span class="n">textcoords</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'offset points'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ha</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'right'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">va</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'bottom'</span>
        <span class="p">)</span>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>First thing we see is this representation exhibits a more organic structure. We see the 4 main subjects from Bukowski's work interwinded across different clusters, and the relationship between word is significantly different from Google's news model. <em>Friend</em>, <em>bitch</em> and <em>whore</em> are clustered together, and seemingly the opposing words <em>kill</em>, <em>die</em>, <em>love</em> and <em>care</em> show up together. Many interesting relationships inherent to his literature show up here.</p>
<p>We can also do some word arithmetics::</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [88]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython2"><pre><span></span><span class="n">model</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">most_similar</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">positive</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'love'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'woman'</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">topn</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
